'''红色森林'''（{{lang-uk|Рудий ліс}}，{{lang-ru|Рыжий лес}}），是指乌克兰[[切尔诺贝利核电站|切尔诺贝利核电站]]方圆十公里内的树林。它現被劃為禁止進入地段，歷經多次的鏟土除汙，仍为世界上污染最严重的地区之一<ref name=partone>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4843316.stm "Chernobyl - Part One"] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4843316.stm |date=20181225154206 }} publisher=[[BBC_News|BBC News]] | Last Updated: Tuesday, 4 April 2006</ref>，不過輻射水平已經大大下降。

== 成因 ==
{{main|切尔诺贝利核事故}}
1986年4月，切尔诺贝利核事故中，4號反應堆對當地土壤、水體和大氣的輻射污染相當於[[廣島與長崎原子彈爆炸|廣島與長崎原子彈爆炸]]的20倍。當中高劑量的直接輻射和其後的[[放射性落下灰|放射性落下灰]]嚴重污染區域內的樹林，这片松树樹林因吸收了过量的放射线导致死亡，並呈棕红颜色<ref name=bbcmulvey>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4923342.stm ''Wildlife defies Chernobyl radiation''] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4923342.stm |date=20181225154205 }}, by Stefen Mulvey, [[BBC_News|BBC News]] April 20, 2006.</ref>，外界皆稱該區域為「紅色森林」。

== 灾后处理 ==
人們已經撤離紅森林區域，大部分受污染的林木被推土機剷平後埋在壕溝内<ref name= WASTEGRAVEYARDS>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4942828.stm ''Chernobyl's continuing hazards''] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4942828.stm |date=20181225154209 }}, by Stefen Mulvey, [[BBC_News|BBC News]]</ref>，然後在上面鋪上厚厚的沙子，並重植松樹樹苗。<ref name=Wormwood>{{cite web |url=http://www.chernobyl.in.ua/en/red_forest |title=''A Natural History of Chernobyl'' |author1=Mary Mycio |publisher=Wormwood Forest: A Natural History of Chernobyl |date=2005 |archivedate=2005-12-14 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051214213112/http://www.chernobyl.in.ua/en/red_forest |language=en |deadurl=yes }}</ref>但許多人擔心，隨著被埋的樹木腐爛分解，輻射會滲入地下水。

==生態現況==
隨著人類自1986年撤離該地區，儘管大大受到事故帶來的核輻射影響，紅色森林內的動植物逐步恢復其生物多樣性。<ref name=environment>[https://web.archive.org/web/20031005140805/http://www.nsrl.ttu.edu/chernobyl/wildlifepreserve.html ''The Chernobyl nuclear disaster and subsequent creation of a wildlife preserve''], Letter to the Editor, Robert J.Baker, Texas Tech University and International Radioecology Laboratory</ref> 有報導指出區域內現增加了一些矮小的植物。野豬的數目亦在1986至1988年之間增長了八倍。<ref name=bbcmulvey/>當前生態狀況基本恢復到有生物定居繁衍的狀態，雖然短期內還不適合人類長居，但針對這些生物的研究還在進行中。
==人類活動==
在2022年2月[[2022年俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭|俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭]]時，據報有俄軍車輛進入紅色森林，將其用作護航的路線，因而揚起了森林中的[[輻射塵|輻射塵]]雲狀物。當地工人報告稱，俄軍駛進紅色森林時並無穿着[[防護服|防護服]]，有可能受到危害<ref>{{Cite news |last=Reuters |date=2022-03-29 |title=Unprotected Russian soldiers disturbed radioactive dust in Chernobyl's 'Red Forest', workers say |language=en |work=[[Reuters|Reuters]] |url=https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/unprotected-russian-soldiers-disturbed-radioactive-dust-chernobyls-red-forest-2022-03-28/ |access-date=2022-03-29}}</ref>。在2022年3月31日，有報告指大部分佔領車諾比的俄軍在嚴重污染的紅色森林挖掘戰壕，隨後患上輻射疾病而被迫撤退<ref>[https://metro.co.uk/2022/03/31/chernobyl-withdrawn-russian-troops-suffering-radiation-poisoning-16377485/ Dozens of Russian troops ‘fall ill with radiation poisoning’ at Chernobyl]</ref><ref>[https://www.thedailybeast.com/russian-troops-suffer-acute-radiation-sickness-after-digging-chernobyl-trenches Russian Troops Suffer ‘Acute Radiation Sickness’ After Digging Chernobyl Trenches]</ref>。烏克蘭官員允許進入該地點之後，發現了大量在紅色森林中挖掘戰壕的證據<ref>[https://www.cnn.com/2022/04/08/europe/chernobyl-russian-withdrawal-intl-cmd/index.html "Ukrainians shocked by 'crazy' scene at Chernobyl after Russian pullout reveals radioactive contamination" by Vasco Cotovio, Frederik Pleitgen, Byron Blunt and Daria Markina, ''CNN'', April 8, 2022.]</ref><ref name = Kramer>[https://www.nytimes.com/2022/04/08/world/europe/ukraine-chernobyl.html?unlocked_article_code=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACEIPuomT1JKd6J17Vw1cRCfTTMQmqxCdw_PIxftm3iWka3DJDm4SiPsSGYyMvErQf617apwu3C6SRdlMdbQvSeZ0yeVOOwptVwys6NOiqagyHh8U-8i1T39kmNXER6w5-jvnKTXpcr51zuC1-hvbaGf1XKTU0Wkqcwo1vcFhIV2gi3YDk6-VFvVnmYUrhYdXDZ5xQzsEYymPrqOoX004YIPaG0mavgomWOhZWiXRmMqe498DdwZUCFHHTRBv8Dp2qYMcaJ5MYvGJf1N3c9H-gL4RFmVvMI6iYpU1TIXWnL9o2qXf2AD7YbTlChgdcDEFVvX0HQ&smid=url-share Andrew E. Kramer, "Russian Blunders in Chernobyl: ‘They Came and Did Whatever They Wanted’ ", ''New York Times'', April 8, 2022.]</ref>。2022年4月1日，《[[每日電訊報|每日電訊報]]》報導稱，一名曾在紅色森林長期紮營的俄羅斯士兵死於[[急性辐射综合症|放射線病]]<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kilner |first=James |date=2022-04-01 |title=Russian soldier dies from radiation poisoning in Chernobyl |language=en-GB |work=The Telegraph |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-news/2022/04/01/russian-soldier-dies-radiation-poisoning-chernobyl/ |access-date=2022-04-02 |issn=0307-1235}}</ref>。

